Create & Disable a User

Lab 4 of n

free website creator
1. Restart VM & Connect via RDP
2. Go to Start & Server Manager

3. Click on the Tools menu and choose Active Directory Administrative Center

4. Click on your server "(local)" and then "Users."

5. Look at the Tasks & Users panel on the right of the screen. Click "New" and then "User."


6. Enter the user details and click OK. 

7. You will now see that the new user has been added. Close the ADAC.

Now we’ll look at a second method to add a user. 

8. From the Server Manager window chose "Tools" and "Active Directory Users & Computers."

9. Click the arrow next to your domain name to expand the menu. Then click "Users."

10. Right click in the white space; click "New" and then "User."

11. Enter the employee's name and user name. Click "Next."

12. Enter a password. Click "Next." 

13. Review the information and click "Finish."

14. You should now see your new user next to the one you created earlier.


TO RESET A PASSWORD
1. Select the user and right click on their listing. Choose "Reset Password" from the menu.

2. Enter a new password for the user. They will be prompted to change it upon login. Then click OK. 


TO DISABLE A USER
1. Select the user and right click on their listing. Choose "Disable User" from the menu. 

You are finished with this lab. You can stop your resource group or continue to the next lab.
